In unimolecular reaction theory, the Rice–Ramsperger–Kassel–Marcus (RRKM) framework treats the microcanonical rate constant as arising from microcanonical transition-state theory (TST). Begin from the flux-over-population viewpoint at fixed total energy, where the numerator is the number of transition-state quantum states that can carry flux across a dividing surface at energy up to a specified excess energy and the denominator is the density of reactant quantum states at the same total energy. Your tasks are as follows, with careful attention to dimensional consistency.

